@startuml UC-003: Start Lab (Get Network Configuration)

title UC-003: Start Lab (Get Network Configuration)
autonumber

actor Student
participant "Client" as Client
participant "Lab API" as API
participant "IPGenerator" as IPGenerator
participant "SessionService" as SessionService
participant "LargeSubnetAllocator" as LargeSubnet
database "MongoDB" as DB

== Start Lab Flow ==
Student -> Client: Click "Start Lab"
Client -> API: POST /labs/:id/start

API -> API: Verify student authentication (JWT)
API -> DB: Fetch lab document
DB --> API: Lab details

API -> API: Verify lab is published
API -> API: Check availability window

alt Lab not available
    API --> Client: 403 Forbidden
    Client --> Student: Lab not available yet
else Lab available
    API -> IPGenerator: generateStudentNetworkConfiguration(lab, studentId)

    IPGenerator -> SessionService: getOrCreateSession(studentId, lab)

    SessionService -> DB: Find active session

    alt Active session exists
        DB --> SessionService: Existing session with IP
    else No active session
        DB --> SessionService: No session found

        SessionService -> SessionService: Calculate available Management IP

        SessionService -> DB: Create new session with unique IP

        alt IP already assigned (race condition)
            DB --> SessionService: Duplicate IP error
            SessionService -> SessionService: Retry with exponential backoff
            SessionService -> DB: Create session with new IP
            DB --> SessionService: Session created
        else IP available
            DB --> SessionService: Session created
        end
    end

    SessionService --> IPGenerator: Return Session (with Management IP)

    alt Large Subnet Mode Enabled
        IPGenerator -> IPGenerator: Check session for existing allocation

        alt Allocation needed (First time or new)
            IPGenerator -> LargeSubnet: allocateSubnet(studentId, labId)
            LargeSubnet -> DB: Fetch all active allocations (collision check)
            DB --> LargeSubnet: Allocated indices
            LargeSubnet -> LargeSubnet: Calculate hash & Resolve collisions
            LargeSubnet --> IPGenerator: Allocation Result (Subnet + VLANs)

            IPGenerator -> DB: Save allocation to Session
        end
    end

    IPGenerator -> IPGenerator: Generate IP Mappings (IPv4/IPv6)
    IPGenerator -> IPGenerator: Generate VLAN Mappings
    IPGenerator -> IPGenerator: Calculate VLAN Subnets

    IPGenerator --> API: Complete network configuration

    API --> Client: 200 OK + network config
    Client --> Student: Show network topology with IPs
end

@enduml
